h601.definition: from {{h599}}; an unclean bird, perhaps the parrot (from its irascibility); heron.

h602.definition: a primitive root; to shriek; cry, groan.

h603.definition: from {{h602}}; shrieking; crying out, groaning, sighing.

h604.definition: the same as {{h603}}; some kind of lizard, probably the gecko (from its wail); ferret.

h605.definition: a primitive root; to be frail, feeble, or (figuratively) melancholy; desperate(-ly wicked), incurable, sick, woeful.

h606.definition: (Aramaic) or אֱנַשׁ; (Aramaic), corresponding to {{h582}}; a man; man,   whosoever.

h607.definition: (Aramaic) corresponding to {{h859}}; thou; as for thee, thou.

h609.definition: of uncertain derivation; Asa, the name of a king and of a Levite; Asa.

h610.definition: from {{h5480}}; anointed, i.e. an oil-flask; pot.

h612.definition: from {{h631}}; a bond (especially manacles of a prisoner); band,   prison.

h614.definition: or אָסִף; from {{h622}}; gathered, i.e. (abstractly) a gathering in of crops; ingathering.

h615.definition: from {{h631}}; bound, i.e. a captive; (those which are) bound, prisoner.

h617.definition: the same as {{h616}}; prisoner; Assir, the name of two Israelites; Assir.

h618.definition: from an unused root meaning to heap together; a storehouse (only in the plural); barn, storehouse.

h619.definition: of uncertain derivation; Asnah, one of the Nethinim; Asnah.

h620.definition: of foreign derivation; Osnappar, an Assyrian king; Asnapper.

h621.definition: of Egyptian derivation; Asenath, the wife of Joseph; Asenath.

h622.definition: a primitive root; to gather for any purpose; hence, to receive, take away, i.e. remove (destroy, leave behind, put up, restore, etc.); assemble, bring, consume, destroy, felch, gather (in, together, up again), × generally, get (him), lose, put all together, receive, recover (another from leprosy), (be) rereward, × surely, take (away, into, up), × utterly, withdraw.

h623.definition: from {{h622}}; collector; Asaph, the name of three Israelites, and of the family of the first; Asaph.

h624.definition: passive participle of {{h622}}; collected (only in the plural), i.e. a collection of offerings; threshold, Asuppim.

h626.definition: from {{h622}}; a collection of people (only adverbial); × together.

h627.definition: feminine of {{h624}}; a collection of (learned) men (only in the plural); assembly.

h628.definition: by reduplication from {{h624}}; gathered up together, i.e. a promiscuous assemblage (of people); mixt multitude.

h629.definition: (Aramaic) of Persian derivation; diligently; fast, forthwith, speed(-ily).

h630.definition: of Persian derivation; Aspatha, a son of Haman; Aspatha.

h631.definition: a primitive root; to yoke or hitch; by analogy, to fasten in any sense, to join battle; bind, fast, gird, harness, hold, keep, make ready, order, prepare, prison(-er), put in bonds, set in array, tie.

h632.definition: or אִסָּר; from {{h631}}; an obligation or vow (of abstinence); binding, bond.

h633.definition: (Aramaic) corresponding to {{h632}} in a legal sense; an interdict; decree.

h634.definition: of foreign derivation; Esarchaddon, an Assyrian king; Esar-haddon.

h635.definition: of Persian derivation; Ester, the Jewish heroine; Esther.

h636.definition: (Aramaic) corresponding to {{h6086}}; a tree or wood; timber, wood.

h637.definition: a primitive particle; meaning accession (used as an adverb or conjunction); also or yea; adversatively though; also, + although, and (furthermore, yet), but, even, + how much less (more, rather than), moreover, with, yea.

h639.definition: from {{h599}}; properly, the nose or nostril; hence, the face, and occasionally a person; also (from the rapid breathing in passion) ire; anger(-gry),   before, countenance, face,   forebearing, forehead,   (long-) suffering, nose, nostril, snout, × worthy, wrath.

h640.definition: a primitive root [rather a denominative from {{h646}}]; to gird on (the ephod); bind, gird.

h641.definition: the same as {{h646}} shortened; Ephod, an Israelite; Ephod.

h642.definition: feminine of {{h646}}; a girding on (of the ephod); hence, generally, a plating (of metal); ephod, ornament.

h643.definition: apparently of foreign derivation; a pavilion or palace-tent; palace.

h644.definition: a primitive root; to cook, especially to bake; bake(-r, (-meats)).

h645.definition: or אֵפוֹא; from {{h6311}}; strictly a demonstrative particle, here; but used of time, now or then; here, now, where?

h646.definition: rarely אֵפֹד; probably of foreign derivation; a girdle; specifically the ephod or highpriest's shoulder-piece; also generally, an image; ephod.

h647.definition: perhaps from {{h6315}}; breeze; Aphiach, an Israelite; Aphiah.

h648.definition: from the same as {{h651}} (in the sense of weakness); unripe; not grown up.

h649.definition: dual of {{h639}}; two nostrils; Appajim, an Israelite; Appaim.

h650.definition: from {{h622}}; properly, containing, i.e. a tube; also a bed or valley of a stream; also a strong thing or a hero; brook, channel, mighty, river,   scale, stream, strong piece.

h651.definition: from an unused root meaning to set as the sun; dusky; very dark.

h652.definition: from the same as {{h651}}; dusk; darkness, obscurity, privily.

h653.definition: feminine of {{h651}}; duskiness, figuratively, misfortune; concrete, concealment; dark, darkness, gloominess, × thick.

h654.definition: from {{h6419}}; judge; Ephlal, an Israelite; Ephlal.

h655.definition: from an unused root meaning to revolve; a turn, i.e. a season; fitly.

h656.definition: a primitive root; to disappear, i.e. cease; be clean gone (at an end, brought to nought), fail.

h657.definition: from {{h656}}; (sometimes like {{h6466}}); cessation, i.e. an end (especially of the earth); often used adverb, no further; also the ankle (in the dual), as being the extremity of the leg or foot; ankle, but (only), end, howbeit, less than nothing, nevertheless (where), no, none (beside), not (any, -withstanding), thing of nought, save(-ing), there, uttermost part, want, without (cause).

h658.definition: from {{h657}} and the plural of {{h1818}}; boundary of blood-drops; Ephes-Dammim, a place in Palestine; Ephes-dammim.

h659.definition: from an unused root probably meaning to breathe; properly, a breath, i.e. nothing; of nought.

h660.definition: from {{h659}} (in the sense of hissing); an asp or other venomous serpent; viper.

h661.definition: a primitive root; to surround; compass.

h662.definition: a primitive root; to contain, i.e. (reflex.) abstain; force (oneself), restrain.

h663.definition: or אֲפִיק; from {{h662}} (in the sense of strength); fortress; Aphek (or Aphik), the name of three places in Palestine; Aphek, Aphik.

h664.definition: feminine of {{h663}}; fortress; Aphekah, a place in Palestine; Aphekah.

h665.definition: from an unused root meaning to bestrew; ashes; ashes.

h666.definition: from the same as {{h665}} (in the sense of covering); a turban; ashes.

h667.definition: from {{h6524}} (in the sense of bursting the shell); the brood of a bird; young (one).

h668.definition: probably of Egyptian derivation; a palanquin; chariot.

h669.definition: dual of masculine form of {{h672}}; double fruit; Ephrajim, a son of Joseph; also the tribe descended from him, and its territory; Ephraim, Ephraimites.

h670.definition: (Aramaic) of foreign origin (only in the plural); an Apherasite or inhabitant of an unknown region of Assyria; Apharsite.

h671.definition: (Aramaic) or אֲפַרְסַתְכַי; (Aramaic), of foreign origin (only in the plural); an Apharsekite or Apharsathkite, an unknown Assyrian tribe; Apharsachites, Apharasthchites.

h672.definition: or אֶפְרָתָה; from {{h6509}}; fruitfulness; Ephrath, another name for Bethlehem; once (Psalm 132:6) perhaps for Ephraim; also of an Israelitish woman; Ephrath, Ephratah.

h673.definition: patrial from {{h672}}; an Ephrathite or an Ephraimite; Ephraimite, Ephrathite.

h674.definition: (Aramaic) of Persian origin; revenue; others at the last; revenue.

h675.definition: or אֶצְבֹּן; of uncertain derivation; Etsbon, the name of two Israelites; Ezbon.

h676.definition: from the same as {{h6648}} (in the sense of grasping); something to sieze with, i.e. a finger; by analogy, a toe; finger, toe.

h678.definition: from {{h680}} (in its secondary sense of separation); an extremity (Isaiah 41:9), also a noble; chief man, noble.

h679.definition: from {{h680}} (in its primary sense of uniting); a joint of the hand (i.e. knuckle); also (according to some) a party-wall (Ezekiel 41:8); (arm) hole, great.

h680.definition: a primitive root; properly, to join; used only as a denominative from {{h681}}; to separate; hence, to select, refuse, contract; keep, reserve, straiten, take.

h681.definition: from {{h680}} (in the sense of joining); a side; (as a preposition) near; at, (hard) by, (from) (beside), near (unto), toward, with. See also {{h1018}}.

h682.definition: from {{h680}}; noble; Atsel, the name of an Israelite, and of a place in Palestine; Azal, Azel.

h683.definition: from {{h680}} and {{h3050}} prolonged; Jah has reserved; Atsaljah, an Israelite; Azaliah.

h684.definition: from an unused root probably meaning to be strong; strength (i.e. strong); Otsem, the name of two Israelites; Ozem.

h685.definition: a variation from {{h6807}}; properly, a step-chain; by analogy, a bracelet; bracelet, chain.

h686.definition: a primitive root; to store up; (lay up in) store,   (make) treasure(-r).

h687.definition: from {{h686}}; treasure; Etser, an Idumaean; Ezer.

h688.definition: from {{h6916}}; burning, i.e. a carbuncle or other fiery gem; carbuncle.

h689.definition: probably from {{h602}}; slender, i.e. the ibex; wild goat.

h690.definition: probably for {{h738}}; lion; Ara, an Israelite; Ara.

h691.definition: probably for {{h739}}; a hero (collectively); valiant one.

h692.definition: from {{h691}}; heroic; Areli (or an Arelite, collectively), an Israelite and his descendants; Areli, Arelites.

h693.definition: a primitive root; to lurk; (lie in) ambush(-ment), lay (lie in) wait.

h694.definition: from {{h693}}; ambush; Arab, a place in Palestine; Arab.

h695.definition: from {{h693}}; ambuscade; den, lie in wait.

h697.definition: from {{h7235}}; a locust (from its rapid increase); grasshopper, locust.

h698.definition: feminine of {{h696}} (only in the plural); ambuscades; spoils.

h699.definition: feminine participle passive of {{h693}} (as if for lurking); a lattice; (by implication) a window, dovecot (because of the pigeon-holes), chimney (with its apertures for smoke), sluice (with openings for water); chimney, window.

h700.definition: plural of {{h699}}; Arubboth, a place in Palestine; Aruboth.
